### 🎯 Objectives
By the end of this midterm project, students will be able to:
1. Derive and mathematically explain the Inverse Kinematics (IK) solution for the Spartan Robokit.
2. Develop a Python-based calculator to compute Inverse Kinematics and visualize the mechanical manipulator's workspace.
3. Integrate Inverse Kinematics into MATLAB to establish a functioning digital twin capable of controlling the physical Spartan Robokit.
4. Experimentally validate the IK model by performing a 5-point position vector test and measuring physical spatial accuracy.
5. Analyze computational IK outputs to classify their operational validity (e.g., correct, FK = IK, mirror, or undefined).

